This product includes original code inspired by, and HTTP/tool contracts
re-implemented from, the following open-source projects. No source code
has been copied verbatim from these projects -- only the publicly
documented HTTP request/response shapes, tool surfaces, and user-facing
conventions are re-used.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Perplexity AI MCP Server  (https://github.com/perplexityai/modelcontextprotocol)
Copyright (c) Perplexity AI
Licensed under the MIT License.

The Perplexity tool surface (`perplexity_search`, `perplexity_ask`,
`perplexity_research`, `perplexity_reason`), the documented request
options (`search_recency_filter`, `search_domain_filter`,
`search_context_size`, `reasoning_effort`, `strip_thinking`), and the
configuration env vars (`PERPLEXITY_API_KEY`, `PERPLEXITY_BASE_URL`,
`PERPLEXITY_TIMEOUT_MS`, `PERPLEXITY_PROXY`) follow this project's
contract so existing operator habits carry over.
Implementation in `src/qwen_coder_mcp/perplexity_tools.py` is original
Python written for this project.

